commits.message:
feat(deploy): add a cfs-deploy tool

Signed-off-by: ytyuanxi <1206812491@qq.com>

issue.title: [Feature]: Optimize CubeFS containerized deployments
issue.body:
### Description of Requirement
- The current CubeFS containerized deployment uses a bash script, which has a single function and only supports one-click deployment and cleanup. It does not support cluster topology modification, single service/role upgrade, one-click upgrade and expansion, cluster operation and maintenance management, etc.
 - The project needs to use the Go language for containerized deployment reconstruction, supports containerized deployment of clusters based on topology files, and supports functions such as one-click upgrade and expansion.
### Project Output Requirements
- Functional documentation of the deployment tool, including functions such as one-click deployment, cleaning, capacity expansion, and upgrade
- According to the documentation, the implementation of the deployment tool code is completed, and the functional verification basically passes
